= TTF_RenderText_Blended_Wrapped =

Create a 32-bit ARGB surface and render the given text at high quality, using alpha blending to dither the font with the given color.

== Syntax ==

<syntaxhighlight lang='c'>
SDL_Surface * TTF_RenderText_Blended_Wrapped(TTF_Font *font,
                const char *text, SDL_Color fg, Uint32 wrapLength);
</syntaxhighlight>

== Function Parameters ==

{|
|'''font'''
|[[TTF_Font]] handle
|-
|'''text'''
|text to render
|-
|'''fg'''
|foreground color
|-
|'''wrapLength'''
|wrap length
|}

== Return Value ==

Returns the new surface, or NULL if there was an error.

== Remarks ==

Text is wrapped to multiple lines on line endings and on word boundaries if
it extends beyond wrapLength in pixels. If wrapLength is 0, only wrap on
new lines. This function returns the new surface, or NULL if there was an
error.

